body:
You guys wanna Feel?

I just got a horrible idea and on the one hand I should keep it to my head but as a story writer I must oblige.

We find Peter Parker, your friendly neighborhood Spiderman, sitting in front of a grave, bawling his eyes out. The name on the grave is of a person on everyone’s lips.

Wade Wilson, Merc with a mouth, self-proclaimed boyfriend of Spiderman, and most importantly, Deadpool, comes up behind him. “What’s got ya torn up Spidey?” He asks. But he knows the answer. He always knows the answer.

“I lost an uncle a long time ago.” Peter chokes out, tears streaming down his face, “And it was still hard to get over.” He sharply inhales, the revelation tearing at him, “But now I’ve lost my dad too.”

Wade sits bedside our distressed do-gooder. He hugs him, offering a small condolence, “I know buddy…I know.”

caption:
Y’know how most superheroes try to, how do I put this, avoid civilian casualties during their fights?

As in, the exact opposite of deliberately trying to lead a flaming Herald of Galactus into crowded office buildings or subway stations, or to blow up an inner city service station?

Gosh, it sure is!

Apparently!
